How do you secure secrets in CI/CD pipelines?

AWS Secrets Manager

Step 1 — Choose secret type:

You are on right page ✅

Select → Other type of secret
         ↑
         API key, OAuth token, other
         This is for our variables
         NOT RDS credentials

Step 2 — Add key value pairs:

Click → Other type of secret
        │
        ▼
Key/Value pairs:

Key                  Value
─────────────────────────────────────
AWS_REGION           us-east-2
ECR_REPO_NAME        pipeline
EKS_CLUSTER_NAME     my-eks-cluster
K8S_NAMESPACE        default
AWS_ACCOUNT_ID       382458445256

Click → Next

Step 3 — Configure secret:

Secret name → /myapp/prod/buildspec-vars
Description → CodeBuild variables for pipeline
Click → Next

Step 4 — Configure rotation:

Automatic rotation → Disable
                     (not needed for config values)
Click → Next

Step 5 — Review:

Review everything
Click → Store ✅

After creating use in buildspec.yml:

env:
  secrets-manager:
    AWS_REGION:       /myapp/prod/buildspec-vars:AWS_REGION
    ECR_REPO_NAME:    /myapp/prod/buildspec-vars:ECR_REPO_NAME
    EKS_CLUSTER_NAME: /myapp/prod/buildspec-vars:EKS_CLUSTER_NAME
    K8S_NAMESPACE:    /myapp/prod/buildspec-vars:K8S_NAMESPACE
    AWS_ACCOUNT_ID:   /myapp/prod/buildspec-vars:AWS_ACCOUNT_ID
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
